news.title: RBI keeps benchmark lending rate unchanged at 4%
news.para: RBI Governor Shaktikanta Das said the monetary policy committee decided to hold the lending rate, or the repo rate, steady at 4 per cent, and its reverse repo, or the rate at which it absorbs excess cash from lenders - unchanged at 3.35 per cent.

news.title: No hike in property tax in Pune civic body limits
news.para: The standing committee of the PMC on Wednesday decided not to increase the property and entertainment tax for the 2022-23 fiscal.

news.title: Vijayawada: 'Walk to work' boon awaits colony residents
news.para: Krishna district administration developed layouts at Nunna, Surampalli, Kondapavuluru, Velagaleru and other villages near Vijayawada and allocated plots to the beneficiaries.

news.title: Telangana: Rs 5,000 penalty on five civic officials over building permits
news.para: The highest number of applications 19 are pending with Mani Bushan for the past 19 working days. “This is a gross violation of the mandate of the government’s TSbPASS Act.

news.title: Chandigarh: Eight freehold residential sites to be auctioned in March
news.para: The eight sites are in sectors 33, 34, 35, 37 and 40. Sector has 40 three sites, Sector 37 two and the remaining sectors one each. The area varies between 250 square yards and 527 square yards.

news.title: Calcutta HC chief justice nominates senior judge for RERA implementation in West Bengal
news.para: The counsel for the state government has informed the Supreme Court about this development while appealing to the top court to not entertain a recent application filed by the Forum for People’s Collective Efforts (FPCE), a pan-India homebuyers’ body that is aiming to push the implementation of RERA in the state.

news.title: Illegal buildings come up in Haryana's Aravalis
news.para: According to the residents, the land, covering a few acres, was grabbed over the past few months. They also claimed that the uncontrolled cutting of several native and foreign tree species, including mesquite, has continued unabated in the area over the past five years.

news.title: KLJ Plasticizers buys 2,000 sq yard bungalow in Delhi for Rs 111 crore
news.para: The property has been sold by Birdie and Birdie realtors, a subsidiary of Fortis Healthcare. The buyer has paid ₹6.66 crore stamp duty to the state government.

news.title: SBI disburses Rs 1.12 lakh crore home loans in FY22
news.para: About 40% of such disbursements came from tier-1 cities while the rest has come from other cities and towns. The average ticket size of such loans is said to be at Rs 34 lakh.

news.title: Sebi directs asset management companies to form audit committee from August
news.para: Sebi said the decision has been taken after taking into account the recommendation of Mutual Fund Advisory Committee and the feedback received from the industry and has come out with detailed outline for role, responsibility, membership and other features of the Audit Committee of AMC.

news.title: Indiabulls Housing Finance's net profit down 8% to Rs 303 crore in Q3 FY22
news.para: "There was an 8 per cent dip in our profitability as our loan book has come down by 13-14 per cent. As we shrink in size the profitability is expected to diminish," its deputy managing director Ashwini Kumar Hooda said.

news.title: Mobilise resources immediately to begin Supertech twin-tower demolition: Noida authority
news.para: The twin-towers are located in Supertech's Emerald Court society in Sector 93A of the city and were coming up in violation of building bye-laws. The SC had in August last year ordered demolition of the illegal structures within three months.

news.title: ACC's net profit declines 40.5% to Rs 280.85 crore in Q3 FY22
news.para: ACC's total revenue from operations in October-December 2021 stood at Rs 4,225.76 crore, a rise of 1.95 per cent as compared with Rs 4,144.72 crore in the year-ago period.

news.title: Prestige Estates' profit up 59% to Rs 93 crore in Q3 FY22
news.para: New Delhi, Feb 9 (PTI) Realty firm Prestige Estates Projects Ltd on Wednesday reported a 59 per cent increase in its consolidated net profit to Rs 93.3 crore for the quarter ended December.  Its net profit stood at Rs 58.7 crore in the year-ago period.

news.title: Evergrande aims to deliver six lakh apartments in 2022
news.para: Hui Ka Yan told staff in a Sunday meeting that the firm aimed to fully restore construction work across China this month, compared with 93.2% at the end of last year, with a goal of delivering 600,000 apartments in 2022, according to a source with direct knowledge of the matter and media reports.
